---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - LocalResizer" description="LocalResizer privacy policy. Static images are processed locally in your browser.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 prose prose-slate">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: March 2026</em></p>
    <h2>The Short Version</h2>
    <p><strong>Your static images are processed locally in your browser.</strong> We do not upload, store, or transmit the images you use in the current tool workflow.</p>
    <h2>Scope of This Policy</h2>
    <p>This policy describes the current public release of LocalResizer, which is limited to static JPEG, PNG, and WebP image workflows that run locally in the browser.</p>
    <h2>What We Collect</h2>
    <p>We use privacy-friendly analytics to understand overall site usage, such as page views and broad traffic patterns. Those analytics describe visits to the site, not the image content you process inside the tool.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>No image files are collected</li>
      <li>No image content is sent to our servers</li>
      <li>No account is required to use the current tool pages</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Support Email Messages</h2>
    <p>If you contact us by email, we receive the information you send, such as your email address, message content, and any troubleshooting details you choose to include. We use that information only to respond to your request, investigate the issue, or improve the current site workflows.</p>
    <h2>What We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your uploaded image content</li>
      <li>The processed image result</li>
      <li>Personal profile data tied to an account, because there is no account system</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We may use third-party services such as privacy-focused analytics or advertising products in the future. If those services materially change the data flow, this policy will be updated.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about privacy? Visit the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
